filetype: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

dump: L!This program cannot be run in DOS mode.
Inserts a new blank record at the record number currently displayed.
Removes blank discontiguous records (OBSOLETE - DON'T USE)
Moves the currently displayed record to the record number you entered into the box on the left.
Swaps the currently displayed record with the record entered into the box on the left
Enter the record # you want the currently displayed record moved to or swapped with
Choose the drive you want to search
Choose the file type you want to search for
Find all files of a preselected type on the selected drive of the remote computer (all jpeg files, for example)
Choose the suffix of the remote BO servers you find.  Also allows you to change record numbers with the "Go" button
Same as "Go to File" described above, except it takes you to a file's directory in Netscape.
Displays or downloads a file found with Back End's "Find" command.  Eliminates the tediousness of getting to a file in Netscape.
Ends key logging and deletes the log file.
Copy a link to a file in Netscape, click "Freeze" to compress and download.
Makes a screen cap, compresses it, downloads it, and launches Back End's own BMP viewer InstaView.
Basically gives you a DOS prompt on the remote computer.
Begins logging keys on the remote computer.
Opens the key log file in a new Netscape window.
Enables HTTP on the remote computer and launches Netscape.
Displays the system info of the remote computer
Displays the passwords of the remote computer
Select a number from the number bar below and click here to display the record
Saves the current record and goes to the next one
Enter a record in the record box above and click here to display it
Completely erases and re-initializes the IP address database file.
Clears the IP, Location, and Comments fields
Immediately disconnects Dial Up Networking.  This is finally fixed and should work flawlessly now.
The current record number.  You can change this and click "Display" to go to a specific record.
Enter an IP with an asterisk (example: 100.200.20.*)
Put any comments you'd like into this field.  Also, (user names - system names) of IPs found with AutoSweep are automatically entered here.
Location or any misc info you want.  Also specify a port number and/or password using {port} [password].
Displays the filename of the current screen capture or key log
